HEADWORD: Electro-bioscopy
<hw>E*lec`tro-bi*os"co*py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Electro-</ets> + Gr. <?/ life + <ets>-scopy</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A method of determining the presence or absence
of life in an animal organism with a current of electricity, by noting
the presence or absence of muscular contraction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electro-capillarity</ent>⟦br⟧
